=\"sby_video_thumbnail_wrap sby_item_video_thumbnail_wrap\">\n            <a class=\"sby_video_thumbnail sby_item_video_thumbnail\" href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=LPUswe0hKkc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-full-res=\"https:\/\/i.ytimg.com\/vi\/LPUswe0hKkc\/maxresdefault.jpg\" data-img-src-set=\"{&quot;120&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/i.ytimg.com\\\/vi\\\/LPUswe0hKkc\\\/default.jpg&quot;,&quot;320&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/i.ytimg.com\\\/vi\\\/LPUswe0hKkc\\\/mqdefault.jpg&quot;,&quot;480&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/i.ytimg.com\\\/vi\\\/LPUswe0hKkc\\\/hqdefault.jpg&quot;,&quot;640&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/i.ytimg.com\\\/vi\\\/LPUswe0hKkc\\\/sddefault.jpg&quot;}\" data-video-id=\"LPUswe0hKkc\" data-video-title=\"Country report on progress on implementation of the Resolutions of the 54th Plenary Assembly.\">\n                <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/plugins\/feeds-for-youtube\/img\/placeholder.png\" alt=\"Hon. Phillipus Katamelo presented Namibia&#039;s country report at the 55th SADC-PF Plenary Assembly in Luanda, Angola on progress on implementation of the Resolutions of the 54th Plenary Assembly. \n\nHe reported that Namibia has made progress in areas such as women and youth representation in parliament. Other notable achievements highlighted are the passing of the Disaster Risk Management Act meant to reduce the effects of floods and drought that perennially plague the country  and the Access to Information Bill aimed at easing access to information in order to empower communities with timely, adequate and accurate information and bridging the digital divide. \n\nThe new Education Act and Child Protection Act are also likely to improve the overall education sector and enhance teaching and learning outcomes and the protection of children from challenges such as child marriage, respectively. Hon. Katamelo stated that the ambitious green hydrogen project will fulfill Namibia\u2019s aspirations of adopting renewable sources of energy  to help de-carbonise and alleviate the energy crisis in the region and beyond. \nHe further implored SADC countries said to already benefit immensely from BRICS countries, to consider  joining the bloc in order to amplify and provide more growth and expansion especilly, inlight of the African Continental Free Trade Area (AfCFTA). The Namibian Parliament has also been raising awareness and advocacy on the universal access to SRHR and HIV and AIDS in collaboration with SADC-PF through its oversight activities. \n#55plenaryassembly #RenewableEnergyForAll\">\n\n                <div class=\"sby_thumbnail_hover sby_item_video_thumbnail_hover\">\n                    <div class=\"sby_thumbnail_hover_inner\">\n                                            <\/div>\n                <\/div>\n\n                                    <div class=\"sby_play_btn\" >\n                        <span class=\"sby_play_btn_bg\"><\/span>\n                        <svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" data-prefix=\"fab\" data-icon=\"youtube\" role=\"img\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 576 512\" class=\"svg-inline--fa fa-youtube fa-w-18\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M549.655 124.083c-6.281-23.65-24.787-42.276-48.284-48.597C458.781 64 288 64 288 64S117.22 64 74.629 75.486c-23.497 6.322-42.003 24.947-48.284 48.597-11.412 42.867-11.412 132.305-11.412 132.305s0 89.438 11.412 132.305c6.281 23.65 24.787 41.5 48.284 47.821C117.22 448 288 448 288 448s170.78 0 213.371-11.486c23.497-6.321 42.003-24.171 48.284-47.821 11.412-42.867 11.412-132.305 11.412-132.305s0-89.438-11.412-132.305zm-317.51 213.508V175.185l142.739 81.205-142.739 81.201z\" class=\"\"><\/path><\/svg>                    <\/div>\n                                <span class=\"sby_loader sby_hidden\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><\/span>\n            <\/a>\n\n                    <\/div>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div><div class=\"sby_item  sby_new sby_transition\" id=\"sb